Fast-Data FTP Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click on "Fast-Data" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "FTP".
4
Enter the FTP IP address in the "IP Address" field.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
FTP has three modes of operation that relate to the handling of server requests.
The default is "standard", but you can also handle requests in "multi-threaded" or
"multi-process" mode.
6
Select the "Custom port" checkbox if you want to use a custom port, instead of the
default (21).
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Enter the custom port in the new "FTP server port" field.
8
Enter the desired number inside the "Maximum number of connection to FTP
server" field.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Enter the maximum number of connections allowed to the FTP server from a
single IP address.
10
Move to "Security".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Click the "+" icon to add a new user credential to the tab. You can also edit,
"pencil" icon, or delete an existing row, "red trash can" icon.
12
After entering the user's credentials, click the 'OK' button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
Move to "Blob settings".
14
The "Blob Settings" tab defines a match between the prefix of the file name (or
several files) "File Name" received from the a4GATE and the folder in the blob
memory "Blob Folder" where the file will be sent. A new row can be added to the
tab by clicking on the "+" icon, an existing line can be modified by clicking on the
"pencil" icon or deleted by clicking on the "red trash can" icon.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
Careful, a single file can be sent only to one folder. The tab has a hierarchial order.
15
Move to "File timestamp".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
16
Click on the "Add timestamp in the name" checkbox, if you want to add the
timestamp of when the file is received by the a4GATE to the original name of the
file.
17
Click on the "Add also milliseconds to timestamp" checkbox if you want your file
name to have also the milliseconds.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
18
You can now click the "Save" button.
19
Select the "FTP service status" to disable the FTP service. After this operation you
will be directed to the "Fast-Data" page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 11
20
Select the "Fast Data FTP service disabled" checkbox to enable FTP service again.
21
You can now return to the FTP page.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 12
22
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
23
Select the required option from "FTP service commands" to start, stop or restart
the FTP service.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 13
24
Select the "Reboot Data Sender" checkbox to reboot the Data Sender. Click the
"Apply" button to start the reboot.
